thread.title: India welcomes new Tourism Secretary

author: eTN Editor
title: India welcomes new Tourism Secretary
text:
India welcomes new Tourism Secretary   
By Anil Mathur, eTN India Correspondent | Sep 03, 2015 Vinod Zutshi   
INDIA (eTN) - Vinod Zutshi has taken over as Secretary, Ministry of Tourism for the government of India. He succeeds Lalit Panwar who has retired. 
Zutshi was earlier Deputy Election Commissioner and has served in the tourism department of Rajasthan. He is from the 1982 batch of Indian Administrative Service and belongs to the Rajasthan cadre. 
Panwar was also from Rajasthan cadre.
